You're joking, right?  I'd like to witness first-hand an EQ loyalist of 3+ years quit EQ because of a mundane flaw such as this.<br>
<br>
People may not forgive and forget this, but that won't matter to Sony as long as they're being paid by the tenacious EQ gamers.  Trust me on this - there are people playing EQ right now that wouldn't quit for the life of them.  There are people playing EQ right now that would rather have one of their limbs severed than lose the reputation and equipment that their character has earned in the past 2-3 years, maybe even less time than that.  People have earnest attachments to their character(s), and it can be extremely hard to separate a gamer from his/her online alter-ego.<br>
<br>
PoP will be good, and the EQ loyalists will appreciate it, cherish it, and love it for what it is, because it IS EQ.  EQ is life for them, and another EQ expansion means not just an expansion to EQ itself, but also as an expansion to their lives.  Long live EQ, and kudos to Sony and Verant for sticking it out.  EQ is the king, and it will remain the king for some time.  When EQ finally gets its crown stolen away from it, it will have easily sucked more than enough money by that time to advocate its sequal.<br>
